This is a demo of using partials in Chef

We can render a partial template using the render method:

<%= render "simple.txt.erb" %>

We can also pass in some custom variables:

<%= render "simple-variables.txt.erb", :variables => {:user => Etc.getlogin } %>

We can also combine partials with normal Erb control flow:

<% @partials.each do |partial, message| %>
  Here is <%= partial %>
<%= render partial, :variables => {:message => message} %>
<% end %>
